 grave RCRA also addresses garbage and industrial waste Common garbage is municipal waste which consists mainly of paper yard trimmings glass and other materials Industrial waste is process waste that comes from a broad range of operations Some wastes are managed by other federal agencies or under state laws Examples of such wastes are animal waste radioactive waste and medical waste Recommended EPA Web pages http www epa gov osw Office of Solid Waste OSW Homepage OSW operates under authority of RCRA protects health environment by insuring responsible mgmt of hazardous and nonhazardous waste http epa gov indicators roe html roeLandWa htm Draft Report on the Environment Better Protected Land Waste and Contaminated Lands Waste is broadly defined as unwanted material or refuse from places of human or animal habitation http www epa gov epaoswer osw topics htm Office of Solid Waste Topics Contains links to EPA documents listed topically within the solid waste subject area http oaspub epa gov webimore aboutepa ebt4 search 21 List more recommended EPA Wastes web pages a name subtopics Browse these EPA Wastes subtopics wastanimalwaste html Animal Waste wasthazardouswaste html Hazardous Waste wasthazardhazardrankingsystemhrs html Hazard Ranking System HRS wasthazardhazardouswastedisposal html Hazardous Waste Disposal wasthazardhazardouswastegeneration html Hazardous Waste Generation wasthazardhazardouswasteidentification html Hazardous Waste Identification wasthazardhazardouswastemanagement html Hazardous Waste Management wasthazardhazardouswasterecycling html Hazardous Waste Recycling wasthazardhazardouswastesite html Hazardous Waste Site wasthazardhazardouswastestorage html Hazardous Waste Storage wasthazardhazardouswastetreatment html Hazardous Waste Treatment wasthazardhouseholdhazardouswaste html Household Hazardous Waste wasthazardradioactivesite html Radioactive Site wasthazarduniversalwaste html Universal Waste wastliquidwaste html Liquid Waste wastliquidusedoil html